review.comments:
This is certainly the place to stay when in Amsterdam! Tastefully furnished, well equipped, and the perfect location. In the heart of the city, yet quiet street overlooking the canal. Beautiful to wake up to and retire to after a long day sightseeing. I stayed with my granddaughter and parents and was looking for a place that would suit all our needs. The beautiful historic yet contemporary luxury style, comfort, ambience and spaciousness definitely fulfilled the check list.  Scented climbing roses greeted us as we arrived, and complimentary Stroopwafel cookies and cool beer got our holiday off to a good start.There is a great option of preparing breakfast and an evening meal in Vandas well equipped kitchen, especially as there is a small supermarket (Spar Shop) just around the corner, for milk, eggs, meat, vegetables and fresh  bread. Kitchen has a good supply of tea, olive oil, salt, sugar, etc.
The square at Rembrantplein with its numerous choice of alfresco restaurants approx 10 minute walk is a great place to eat out and watch the world go by. From the moment we made enquiries with Vanda, to the moment we checked out, communication was exceptional, her hospitality can be felt from across the globe. Vanda is very knowledgable and a great source of information. There are numerous maps, tour books and guides at the property. If you are staying for a very limited time, try and plan your schedule and sites to visit beforehand to maximize your time.
There is absolutely nothing to dislike at Vandas property, we would certainly return again, and highly recommend to our family and friends of every age!
